Long_Name: William K New Sullivan Elementary School
Student_Growth_Description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that started in the same place. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: 5Essentials is based on the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey of teachers and 6th-12th grade students. To see the complete report for your school, visit  https://www.5-essentials.org/ .
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn 90% of all criteria to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  cps.edu/healthycps .
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school has an arts designation of Incomplete Data, meaning it may or may not meet the goals and priorities of the CPS Arts Education Plan, but has insufficient data available to complete an assessment.  To learn more, visit:  http://www.cpsarts.org/ .
Supportive_School_Award_Desc: This school has developed an action plan to support social and emotional learning (SEL). Leaders and staff have assessed their school climate, and they are beginning to adopt best practices to support SEL for all students.

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
Culture_Climate_Description: 5Essentials is based on the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey of teachers and 6th-12th grade students. To see the complete report for your school, visit  https://www.5-essentials.org/ .
Healthy_School_Certification_Description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn 90% of all criteria to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  cps.edu/healthycps .
Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school has an arts designation of Incomplete Data, meaning it may or may not meet the goals and priorities of the CPS Arts Education Plan, but has insufficient data available to complete an assessment.  To learn more, visit:  http://www.cpsarts.org/ .
Supportive_School_Award_Desc: This school has a strong commitment and robust systems to support social and emotional learning (SEL). Supportive_School_Award_Desc: This school has put in place systems and structures to support social and emotional learning (SEL). Student_Growth_Description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time. Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.

Creative_School_Certification_Descriptio: This school has an arts designation of Incomplete Data, meaning it may or may not meet the goals and priorities of the CPS Arts Education Plan, but has insufficient data available to complete an assessment.  To learn more, visit:  http://www.cpsarts.org/ .
Supportive_School_Award_Desc: This school has not submitted an action plan to support school climate and social & emotional learning (SEL).

Student_Growth_Description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that started in the same place. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.

Student_Attainment_Description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time. This school's score is based on attainment relative to the combined College Readiness Benchmark scores, set by College Board. To learn more, visit  https://collegereadiness.collegeboard.org .
